        <h2>One Rule to Remember</h2>
        <p>
          AI tools are powerful, but they are not magic. They reduce the amount of human attention required — but they do not eliminate the need for it. An AI email filter will catch 99% of phishing attempts, which means 1% still get through. Your team still needs to know the red flags.
        </p>
        <p>
          Think of AI security tools as a force multiplier. They handle the volume, the patterns, and the known threats so you can focus your limited human attention on the edge cases that matter.
        </p>

